cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL

This paper is about video summarization, which is a task related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel generative adversarial network (GAN) architecture, which involves training a generator and a discriminator in an adversarial manner, and this is a popular technique in the field of deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves processing and analyzing large amounts of video data, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the use of a discriminator to enforce information completeness and compactness, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
